(1828, 1, '2018-03-28 23:48:24', '2018-03-28 23:48:24', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Web Developer - Wordpress</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A Web Developer / Project Manager with overall experience of more than 5 years in web development.\r\nCurrently, I work exclusively with Wordpress projects and delve deeper into the core of Wordpress API. I wanted to specialize and get a good grip on just one CMS to craft and deliver the best quality projects for my clients. An honest, hardworking professional and always aiming for the best outcome of my craft. I can work with less supervision but I always make sure that I adhere to my client\'s expectation and standards.\r\nI strongly believe that it is vital for developers to follow certain coding standards and best practices to have an easy-to-follow maintainable code. That\'s why I took some preparations before diving into the battlefield, and finished around 14 - Online Courses from Lynda, Udemy, Tutsplus (almost a year).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Moreover, I enjoy working and focus more on developing websites from micro to small-scale business (SME) projects. I can build customized Wordpress Themes from scratch.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Wordpress - Web Development (what I know):</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">- Building Dynamic Wordpress Site\r\n- Building Wordpress Themes from Scratch\r\n- Building Child Themes\r\n- Custom Theme Development\r\n- Theme Structure &amp;amp; Hierarchy Best Practices\r\n- WordPress Plugin Development (a few experiences using OOP &amp;amp; Structural code)\r\n- Wordpress API - Action &amp;amp; Filter Hooks (Basic)\r\n- Using Bootstrap 4 Wordpress Integration - Responsive (desktop / tablets / mobile)\r\n- Wordpress with SASS (NPM &amp;amp; Gulp)\r\n- Custom Post Types and Taxonomies &amp;amp; Custom Fields\r\n- Implement Short Codes in Plugins (Basic)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">A SUMMARY of some of my knowledge &amp;amp; experiences:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">CMS: Wordpress&amp;amp; Drupal (Drupal Developer for around 3-years)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Languages, Compilers, Frameworks &amp;amp; Preprocessors:\r\n- Main: HTML, CSS, PHP, &amp;amp; jQuery, MySQL, Javascript (a bit), Bootstrap, SASS (npm &amp;amp; gulp just recently)\r\n- Others: Turbo Pascal, Clipper, TASM, COBOL, DBase III, Visual Basic, Visual C++, etc. &amp;amp; JAVA (Android Development - 2017).\r\n- Codeigniter Framework, Laravel Framework (Just to show some languages I learned back in the day).</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">O/S: Windows 10 &amp;amp; predecessors, Linux Systems(Ubuntu)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Web Developer Software &amp;amp; Tools:\r\n- ATOM IDE, Netbeans IDE, MySQL Workbench, HeidiSQL, Android Studio, XAMPP, LAMPP, WAMPP, Vagrant, Eclipse PDT, Notepad++, Github, Bitbucket, CS6 Photoshop\r\nProject Management Apps &amp;amp; Tools:\r\n- Trello w/ Timesheets, Dropbox, Slack, Slaask, Basecamp, Onenote, Google Analytics, MS Office\r\nCommunication Tools:\r\n- Skype, Slack, Telegram, FB Messenger\r\nDomain Registrar Management:\r\n- MX Records, Subdomain, Domain Forwarding, Aliases, MX Tools, Email Aliases etc.\r\n- (GoDaddy, Bluehost, CrazyDomains, Netregistry &amp;amp; other accredited registrars in USA, UK &amp;amp; Australia)\r\nEmail Services &amp;amp; Marketing Apps:\r\n- Zoho Mail, MailChimp, Google Mail\r\nContent Delivery Network:\r\n- Cloudflare (DNS &amp;amp; Security Services)\r\nQuality Assurance (Web):\r\n- Selenium\r\nSocial Media:\r\n- HootSuite (handles Facebook, Twitter, Google+, Instagram)\r\nHelpdesk Service:\r\n- Freshdesk, Helpy.io\r\nE-commerce:\r\n- Abantecart, Ubercart (Drupal)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">If you read my background summary and managed to get this far =), you might want to know why? Well, you might be surprised why I charge low for now, I resigned in our company just to get enough experience, &amp;amp; decided to get back in freelancing hoping someday I can build my own company. Though I am a bit new to Wordpress exclusive projects (former Drupal Developer for around 3 years), I am GIVING 50% (from $10) LESS charging rate for my 1st (3-5) solid projects. Hence, I am seeking opportunities wherever I can to extend my skills.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For a start, I wanted to do small-scale projects for a refresher /warmup. Preferred projects that I am interested in:\r\n- Build Wordpress Dynamic Websites from SCRATCH (Small Business, Portfolio, Blog, Restaurants etc.)</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">FYI, to know more about me &amp;amp; verify, I have LinkedIn Account. If interested, I am reachable thru Skype, Hangout, Gmail. I also have a US/Canada Landline Contact # (Obitalk VoIP) w/c you can call directly so we can have a good chat</p>\r\n\r\n<h5 class=\"text-light xs-mb1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B6MTMradTQhZZTZTQTlHTUpHWUk/view\">Employment and education history</a></h5>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"></p>', 'Get to know me more...', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'get-to-know-me-more', '', '', '2018-03-28 23:48:24', '2018-03-28 23:48:24', '', 0, 'http://site1.net/?page_id=1828', 0, 'page', '', 0),
